page.title: 05Population
page.content: The population of this area is 141. Since there is 6.67 sq.km. land area, this means that there are 21 people per sq.km. The population is made up of 72 females and 69 males. Between the ages of 0 and 4 there are 4 people, between the ages of 5 and 12 there are 14 people, between 13 and 18 there are 16 people and between the ages of 18 and 69 there are 93 people. This is an area of considerable population change because we note that, of the 63 houses, only 11 contain families which have at least one member a native of the parish; this represents 17%. There are few young people in the area and yet the population is not falling for several new houses have been built recently.
